 President, LCCI, Babatunde Ruwase  While lauding the 5-year plan of the Central Bank of Nigeria, the Chamber argued that the role of the CBN is in using monetary policies to stimulate economic growth, noting that some of the planned targets are fiscal in nature. “It will therefore require that a framework for collaboration with the major economic ministries and other stakeholders be put in place to be able to fully actualise what the CBN sets out to accomplish in the next five years,” the LCCI added.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .